rb laughlin doctorate of letters doctorate of letters prof robert b laughlin department of physics stanford university stanford ca 94305 prof laughlin received this honorary degree from the university of maryland after delivering the graduation address at its overseas program at yongsan base in seoul korea joe arden the university of maryland's vice president of overseas operations conferred the degree this particular honor has international relations overtones and has been won previously by such luminaries as edwin o reischauer and mike mansfield both of whom served as ambassador to japan among other things prof laughlin had the privilege at this event of meeting ambassador christopher hill and vietnamese poet mong lan whose book song of the cicadas he particularly liked
